  - `cd /testbed && git status`
  - `cd /testbed && git diff`
- Sanity-check you’re testing the right thing:
  - `cd /testbed && python -c "import jinja2; print(jinja2.__file__)"`
    Expect `/testbed/src/jinja2/__init__.py`, not site-packages.
  - If pytest output shows a suspiciously small number of tests (e.g., 26 instead of ~800+), you’re not running the intended suite.
    Fix by running: `cd /testbed && pytest -q /testbed/tests`
- Search patterns that quickly locate the implementation:
